From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Onix Research <dev@onix.computer>
Date: Mon, 29 Jun 2026 12:30:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Bluetooth: btusb: add Foxconn MT7925 0489:e13a

Linux master classifies Foxconn/Hon Hai USB product 0489:e13a as an
additional MediaTek MT7925 Bluetooth device. The ASUS ProArt
X870E-CREATOR WIFI in britton-desktop exposes that product ID for its
Bluetooth controller; without this ID, btusb binds generically and the
controller fails HCI reset during setup.
---
 drivers/bluetooth/btusb.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/bluetooth/btusb.c b/drivers/bluetooth/btusb.c
--- a/drivers/bluetooth/btusb.c
+++ b/drivers/bluetooth/btusb.c
@@ -734,6 +734,8 @@ static const struct usb_device_id quirks_table[] = {
 						     BTUSB_WIDEBAND_SPEECH },
 	{ USB_DEVICE(0x0489, 0xe139), .driver_info = BTUSB_MEDIATEK |
 						     BTUSB_WIDEBAND_SPEECH },
+	{ USB_DEVICE(0x0489, 0xe13a), .driver_info = BTUSB_MEDIATEK |
+						     BTUSB_WIDEBAND_SPEECH },
 	{ USB_DEVICE(0x0489, 0xe14e), .driver_info = BTUSB_MEDIATEK |
 						     BTUSB_WIDEBAND_SPEECH },
 	{ USB_DEVICE(0x0489, 0xe14f), .driver_info = BTUSB_MEDIATEK |
-- 
2.50.0
